Flambeau Hard case
Full box of Federal 150 gr soft points
16/20 rds of Winchester 150 gr Ballistic Silver tips

I've had the rifle for several years and it has probably less than 200 rds through it. I bought this rifle because I might go elk hunting one day. Well several years later I haven't hunted with a rifle in awhile and I never take this rifle to the range because it's got too much recoil for me. I have taken a deer and a hog in Florida with this rifle and if you hit them anywhere in the body, they will not go far.

The rifle is sighted in at 100 yds within about an inch. I don't have a lead sled or the fortitude to get it any closer free hand.

If your looking for a rifle for a deer stand, especially one in a field, this rifle's for you. I wanted something with a flat trajectory so I could take it elk hunting one day. Check out 7mm RM ballistics on the internet; if you sight in at 100 yds, you should be able to hit a deer inside of 300 yds without much trouble at all.

-I have more pictures, but they're too large to upload to this listing; email me if you'd like to see more.

I seem to have a lot of people ask for pictures and not know anywhere close to what these are valued at. Just search Armslist, gunbroker, or buds and you can get more of an idea. 

It's a Rock River Arms LAR-8 (.308), in Mid-length (16") barrel A4 configuration which has a flat top, fwd site base gas block with sling attachment, Hogue grip, 6 position stock. Comes with 3-20round mags and uses the FAL surplus mags which are inexpensive online and at gun shows. The 308 gives you the power and size to hunt large game and gives you a lot more range due to the projectile mass as compared to .223 while also having the ability to be a close combat semi-auto weapon. Also gives you way more muzzle velocity and several feet less bullet drop than the 7.62x39 past 250 yards.

The scope is a Leapers 1x4 combat scope with illuminated red/green reticle on a low profile base which has long eye relief. With a 1x4 you can crank it down and use it like a close combat red dot or bump it up to 4x to take 300 yard shots. The mounts are weaver quick release. The sling is a heavy padded combat sling that adjusts and has neoprene sleeves on the steel buckles so it doesnt make noise or scratch the finish. 200 rounds of federal, 40 rounds of winchester core lock. The nylon bag is padded with a sling to carry on your back with mag pouches in the front. 

I need $1100 for the rifle with 3 mags

title: For Sale:  Silencerco 22 Sparrow
postcontent:
Manufacturer: Silencerco



Model: SS Sparrow (NFA Item) 



Caliber/Gauge: .22 LR



Finish: Matte Black



Approx. Length:  5.08"



Condition: New in Box



Description: 


 The SS 22Sparrow is the first silencer in the world to offer the patent pending Multi Part Containment (MPC) technology, which allows the 22Sparrow to be easily disassembled for cleaning and maintenance after heavy use. 

Because the .22 LR round is not copper jacketed, molten lead and carbon debris will explode into the silencer when the projectile exits the muzzle. After some time, it is possible for a .22 suppressor to fill completely with lead and become heavy and ineffective. To avoid this issue, .22 silencers must be disassembled for cleaning and regular maintenance. 

Until Silencerco introduced the 22Sparrow, the only .22 silencers that could be disassembled for cleaning required a cleaning every 50 to 200 rounds. However, often the components of those silencers would be fused together and unable to come apart. Competitor products on the market have baffles in their .22 silencers that must be removed by twisting the outer tube around the baffles and/or sliding the outer tube off of the baffles. When the lead and carbon debris adhere to the inner wall of the outer tube and fill the spaces between the baffles and the outer tube, there is simply too much buildup of fouling and lead to remove the outer tube in that manner.

Silencerco solved this maintenance issue with MPC technology and made it possible for shooters to disassemble the 22Sparrow easily after heavy use without the need of tools. MPC technology revolutionized take-apart silencers by containing the lead and carbon debris to prevent the debris from reaching the outer tube. This innovative design is achieved by applying two tube halves before sliding the outer tube on the rest of the assembly. When disassembling, the outer tube can be easily removed, and the tube halves are free to pull away from the baffles without having to rotate or slide. Just pull off the tubes, clean the components, and reassemble. 


This is a NFA / Class 3 item and is subjuct to all NFA/ATF regulations. It is subject to a $200 tax. This item will transfer tax free on a form 3 to out of state buyers. You are responsible for finding a class 3 dealer in your state to handle the transfer.

title: For Sale:  Walther P38
postcontent:
For sale is a WW2 Walther P38 9mm handgun with one magazine.  This Walther has the bakelite grips and has matching serial numbers.  The gun is in very good condition and the rifling in the barrel is in very good condition as well.  Don't be fooled by other adds that advertise to have a P38 when in fact they have a P1.  The P1 was a post war gun that was produced out of aluminum and steel.  These are not as valuable or as well built as a real WW2 P38 pistol.  

This is a great gun not only for collecting but for shooting too. These historic guns are becoming harder and harder to find, so add this one to your collection today!  700 or best offer.  700 is a fair price for this particular pistol.

postcontent:
I am selling a Tucker "The Answer" holster, a leather/kydex hybrid inside-waist-band holster, see http://www.tuckergunleather.com/the-answer-iwb/. Asking $110 cash FTF.

This particular holster is made for the Glock 26/27/33 pistol, right-handed, with the leather-lined kydex option. Comes with heavy-duty MTAC clips (http://www.comp-tac.com/product_info.php?products_id=81) for 1.5" wide belts. Also fits Glock 19/23, muzzle will peek past the kydex, but covered on the leather side. In excellent condition, as shown in photos (carried for just a couple months, but ended up selling the pistol).

I have tried many of the other IWB holsters of this style (think CrossBreed ST, MTAC, etc). They are all good, but the Answer has the highest-quality hardware and build, least amount of surface area, and most careful attention to detail. The suede backing greatly improves comfort and the leather-lined kydex protects finish and quiets the draw. If you are looking for top-shelf, this is it.

Looking for a Glock shooter who can give this excellent holster a good home, this may be the last holster you ever buy! Comes with Allen wrench for adjusting ride height and cant.

This is my current carry holster (but for an M&P), so happy to answer any questions you may have.

Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale/Trade:  It's a 1942 Mosin–Nagant  M91/30 made in Izhevsk (Soviet Union) comes with everything in the picture including the 50+ rounds of 7.62×54R ammo.
postcontent:
The Mosin–Nagant (Russian: Винтовка Мосина, ISO 9: Vintovka Mosina) is a bolt-action, internal magazine-fed, military rifle invented under the government commission by Russian and Belgian inventors, and used by the armed forces of the Russian Empire, the Soviet Union and various other nations.

The 7.62×54mmR is a rimmed rifle cartridge developed by the Russian Empire and was introduced as a service cartridge in 1891. Originally designed for the bolt-action Mosin–Nagant rifle, it was used during the late Tsarist era and throughout the Soviet period to the present day. The cartridge remains one of the few standard issue rimmed cartridges still in military use and has the longest service life of all military issued cartridges in the world.
